MESSAGE.value: Adding a way to visually check up on the hot swaps, in case that turns out to be relevant to observed strange behavior.
Skipping the fancy optimizers, just using adaptive rate learning, which seems to work just fine in practice, for some reason. Still are things that need debugging.
Wrote a system to handle progressive saving to partial analysis, to avoid some of the tedium of waiting for long runs.
Checking in some stuff.
Making some fixes to training race conditions.
Added word2vec features for the NER task, so that we can hopefully get a much prettier learning curve.

Switching to a new optimizer (AdaGrad with custom convergence criteria), on the hypothesis that LBFGS was having a hard time converging because of some bug in the system someplace, so is giving me spurious results.
Further tweaking adagrad convergence criteria
Minor experimental tweaks.
Fixed up convergence criteria now that measuring against proper optimized value. Thinking about adding a line-search.
Further tweaking convergence criteria. Seems I should just basically let it run forever. Still don't understand why re-initialization results in massive spikes in error...
Further experimenting with the ideal convergence criteria. Basically longer runs seem unambiguously necessary.
Added a dynamic learning rate as an experiment. We'll see how that goes...
Added a dynamic regularization as an experiment. We'll see how that goes...
Have baby MTurk tests working correctly, setup SSL, did JS work, now need confirmation code for pool stay-time.
Mturk modification to point to shiny new static IP.
Adding machinery for paying bonuses to workers from server-side, according to a handshake after completion of stay.
Frontend is a tangled mess, needs some serious attention after dinner.
Finished for the day
Improving frontend with better instructions, adding shortcut keys, etc.
Added hotkeys, which actually seem to not suck. Now need to make instructions dismissable, etc.
Transition to Jetty 9 seems to fix issues with dropping websocket connections. Hope that's just the end of it.
Made such pretty.
Changed to a simplified NER setup.
Added a bunch of logic to try to make sure we don't accidentally stiff real workers.
